Package com.cafean.CalcServer

Class CalcJobFile

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.CalcServer.CalcJobFile
  • public final class CalcJobFile
extends java.lang.Object
    A wrapper class for a Calculation Job File (CJF, *.cjf).

    The Calculation Job File (CJF) format (*.cjf) is intended to be a replacement for the legacy .status files. This format should be as fast as possible to read and parse as the contents of these files will not be cached or stored in memory unless explicitly requested by a client application.

    Values that are not available in a particular CJF (such as calculation time, end time, etc.) should be simply shown as Unavailable in client applications until a JobHandle has been created.

    Once the JobHandle has been created and the run data loaded into memory the CJF will be updated.

    Note: The CJF file must start with a token (#!CJF2) indicating that it is a valid *.cjf file.

        Note that this property indicates the user's requested interactive status not the current state of the job. If set to true, this property will remain true even after a job has completed, unloaded and reloaded.

      • setFile

        public void setFile​(java.lang.String key,
                    java.io.File file)
        Sets the given file in this CJF with the given key.

        Note: Each file used and/or created by a job must be included in it's CJF as the plug-in may or may not be notified when the job is moved, renamed or removed.

        Parameters:
        key - a String containing the file reference's key. This parameter will be converted to upper case.
        file - the File to store as a path on the local file system.

        Returns:
        the File requested or null if no file is stored with the given key.
